@startuml Attribute Level Security Setup Flow
title Demo App Flow: Attribute Level Security (ALS) Setup

actor "Data Governance\n(Admin)" as Admin
participant "Governance UI" as UI
participant "SecurityConfigController" as Controller
participant "GovernanceManager\n(Service)" as Governance
database "Database" as DB

== Loading the Matrix ==
Admin -> UI : Open "Data Governance" Tab
activate UI
UI -> Controller : GET /security
activate Controller
Controller -> DB : Select Available Models & Roles
activate DB
DB --> Controller : Models & Roles Data
deactivate DB
Controller --> UI : Render View
deactivate Controller

Admin -> UI : Select Model (e.g., 'User') & Role (e.g., 'Analyst')
UI -> Controller : GET /security/matrix?model_class=...&subject_id=...
activate Controller
Controller -> Governance : GovernanceManager::getMatrix()
activate Governance
Governance -> DB : Fetch dynamic_attribute_restrictions
activate DB
DB --> Governance : Existing Restrictions
deactivate DB
Governance --> Controller : Matrix Payload (attributes + is_reportable)
deactivate Governance
Controller --> UI : JSON Data
deactivate Controller
UI --> Admin : Render Toggle Switches & Selectors

== Saving the Matrix ==
Admin -> UI : Change Rule (e.g., Email -> Masked)
Admin -> UI : Click "Save Changes"
UI -> Controller : POST /security/save (JSON Payload)
activate Controller
Controller -> Governance : GovernanceManager::saveMatrix()
activate Governance

note right: Service manages creating, updating, or deleting\nrules based on 'unrestricted', 'masked', or 'blocked'.

Governance -> DB : BEGIN TRANSACTION
activate DB
Governance -> DB : DELETE/INSERT dynamic_attribute_restrictions
Governance -> DB : COMMIT
DB --> Governance : Success
deactivate DB

Governance --> Controller : void
deactivate Governance

Controller --> UI : Success Response
deactivate Controller
UI --> Admin : Show "Saved!" Notification
deactivate UI

@enduml
